16 WHEREAS, in 1999, Brinca advocated for the Olmstead Law, affirming the rights of
17 individuals with mental health conditions and intellectual disabilities to live in their
18 communities; and
19 WHEREAS, Brinca has led numerous community initiatives, including organizing block
20 parties to promote voter participation; partnering with Lady T's Homeless Ministry to provide
21 meals for more than 900 unhoused individuals each week; sponsoring a pocketbook drive
22 that distributed over 200 purses filled with personal hygiene items to homeless girls, women,
23 and children; and coordinating a winter hat drive that provided over 100 personally knitted
24 warm caps to unhoused individuals; and
25 WHEREAS, she has established a glowing reputation of renown throughout Georgia for her
26 leadership as a board member for New Kids Productions, as chair of the Lithonia Community
27 District, and as creator of "The Equalyzer," a community advocacy and activism podcast; and
28 WHEREAS, it is abundantly fitting and proper that the outstanding accomplishments of this
29 extraordinary servant leader be appropriately recognized.
30 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES that
31 the members of this body congratulate and commend Brinca Y. McMickens for receiving the
32 2025 Yellow Rose Nikki T. Randall Servant Leadership Award and extend best wishes for
33 her continued success.
34 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Clerk of the House of Representatives is authorized
35 and directed to make an appropriate copy of this resolution available for distribution to
36 Brinca Y. McMickens.
